# Qualified-types tests excluded from -Ytest-pickler.
#
# The following four tests have qualifiers that reference the enclosing
# method (a self-recursive call inside the qualifier annotation), e.g.
# `def fib(n: Int): {res: Int with res == fib(n - 1) + fib(n - 2)} = ...`.
# Unpickling the method's signature reads the annotation tree, which
# contains an `Apply(Ident(fib), ...)` whose type is computed via
# `tpd.Apply` -> `assignType` -> `fn.tpe.widen`, forcing `fib`'s info
# while it is still being read -> cyclic-reference assertion.
self_reference.scala
fib_selfify.scala
fib_memoized.scala
fib_memoized2.scala

# checked_array2 has a qualifier whose ENode body contains an `Atom(SkolemType)`
# (typically introduced by `asSeenFrom` on an unstable prefix). `toTree`
# encodes such a `SkolemType` as `Predef.undefined` with the SkolemType
# carried on `tree.tpe` via `withType`. TASTy does not preserve that
# override on Idents, so on unpickle the `Ident(Predef.undefined)` has
# `.tpe = Nothing` and `ENode.fromTree` cannot reconstruct the original
# atom -- the annotation decode fails with "invalid tree for QualifiedAnnotation".
checked_array2.scala
